Kwara State Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq has hailed the say-no-die spirit of medical personnel in the fight against COVID-19 pandemic in the state. He attributed his administration’s achievements in the health sector in the past three years to the contributions of the workforce.   Ogun to introduce ‘water kiosking’     Council presents gifts to first Baby-of-the-Year     Lagos APC chair hails Faleke for lifting constituents   The governor hailed professional health care personnel for coming up with ideas, which he said had helped in revamping health care infrastructures. He described his former special adviser on health matters, Prof Wale Sulaiman and his league of experts, as thoroughbred professionals. AbdulRazaq said Sulaiman’s achievements within a year in service were well recognised by all and sundry.